      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STUDLEIGH SUNRISE (3) performed admirably again last start, settling back in the field from a very wide barrier before making up plenty of ground for third at this venue. That was her fourth placing from her last five starts and a low draw could see her break through. HOOKED ON WINNING NZ (9) is racing well, placing in three of four starts since winning at this circuit and distance. Turned in a strong effort from this row at his latest appearance when runner-up, beaten 2 metres. Shouldn't spend a penny from this draw and the sprint lane may come in handy. Leading hope. An early break proved costly for DEAR DARLING (5) last start but she scored back-to-back wins last month so is capable of much better. RIVIERE (6) is worth plenty of thought after coming from a similar barrier and finding form with a last-start win by 7 metres at this venue.",
